<p>I have successfully followed the guide <a href="https://developers.google.com/android/guides/api-client" rel="nofollow">Accessing Google APIs</a>.</p>  <p>After that I have decided to move some of the code into fragment:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/V1f0J.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/V1f0J.jpg" alt="screenshot"></a></p>  <pre><code>&lt;FrameLayout     xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"     android:layout_width="match_parent"     android:layout_height="match_parent"&gt;      &lt;com.google.android.gms.common.SignInButton         android:id="@+id/login_button"         android:layout_width="wrap_content"         android:layout_height="wrap_content"         android:layout_gravity="center"         android:clickable="true"         android:onClick="googleLogin" /&gt;  &lt;/FrameLayout&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And in the MainActivity I have moved GoogleApiClient object creation from <code>onCreate()</code> to <code>googleLogin()</code> method:</p>  <pre><code>public void googleLogin(View v) {     mGoogleApiClient = new GoogleApiClient.Builder(this)             .addConnectionCallbacks(this)             .addOnConnectionFailedListener(this)             .addApi(Plus.API)             .addScope(Plus.SCOPE_PLUS_PROFILE)             .build();      mGoogleApiClient.connect(); } </code></pre>  <p>However the method is never called (as I see in debugger).</p>  <p>What is wrong here, is it a bug (ignoring <code>onClick</code> XML attribute) in the current <a href="https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/android/gms/common/SignInButton" rel="nofollow">SignInButton</a> implementation?</p>